comment:
Let us start at the beginning.  *Before Amber Heard met Johnny Depp, she was in a "domestic partnership" (married) to Tasya van Ree.*  At the time. Ms. Heard had changed her name to Amber van Ree.  *On September 14, 2009, at the Seattle/Tacoma International Airport, Amber Heard was arrested for the domestic assault of her partner, Tasya van Ree.*  Ms. van Ree was struck and police documents show a valuable piece of jewelry was ripped from her neck.  The assault took place in front of an airport full of people and the arresting officers.  Tasys van Ree requested the arrest. Amber Heard was booked, and her mug shot taken, and as Ms. van Ree did not bail her out, Ms. Heard was forced to spend the night in jail.  She was arraigned the next day in King County District Court, where, because both women lived in another state, the prosecutor and Judge agreed to allow the arrest to remain open for a period of two years, in case Ms. Heard should re-offend, or Ms. van Ree should desire to prosecute.

When Ms. Heard met Mr. Depp, she attempted to have this arrest expunged from her record.  Fortunately, Airports must keep duplicate records of arrests.  When the press broke the story in June 2016, Amber Heard was eager to limit the damage, and had Ms. van Ree release a statement "In 2009, Amber was wrongfully accused for an incident that was misinterpreted and over-sensationalized by two individuals in a powerful position.  I recount hints of misogynistic attitudes towards us which later appeared to be homophobic when they found out we were domestic partners and not just 'friends'.  Charges were quickly dropped and she was released moments later."  This statement is full of lies and inconsistencies, which garnered even more attention when the arresting officer, Officer Beverly Leonard, an openly gay woman, Gay Rights Activist, and volunteer at numerous domestic violence shelters, released *her* own statement.  "I am *so* not Homophobic or Misogynistic.  The arrest was made because an assault occurred (I witnessed it) and the parties were in a domestic relationship."

Once again Amber Heard spins a web of lies to extricate herself from her own violence.  Tasya van Ree's statement omits the fact that Ms. van Ree *herself* was responsible for the arrest.  Ms. Heard *certainly wasn't* released moments later.  For proud gay women, they certainly turn on another gay women when it suits their purpose.  This domestic assault happened, and this arrest happened.  Amber Heard was a domestic abuser from 2009.  *SHE NEVER SHOULD HAVE BEEN CONSIDERED FOR THE ROLE OF MERA!*  Mr. Depp has *never* been arrested for domestic assault.  Mr. Dep has *never* been charged with domestic assault.  If EQUAL RIGHTS are ever going to be realized, women have to be held accountable for their actions!
